From 5b59841a0b2c62235557c39f94e8e91e5d13f223 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:16:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix production 500s: add missing core migrations, harden
 admin/security/logging

Root cause of the /admin/core/match/ 500 error: the core app had zero
migration files, so core_match/core_channel/core_news never existed in
Postgres. Added the initial migration.

Also:
- Wire ADMIN_SITE_HEADER/TITLE/INDEX_TITLE into admin.site (previously
  dead settings that were never applied)
- Add explicit console LOGGING so request errors show up in Railway
  deploy logs instead of silently going to mail_admins
- Add production security settings (SSL redirect, secure cookies, HSTS)
  gated on DEBUG so local dev is unaffected
- Add ensure_superuser management command driven by DJANGO_SUPERUSER_*
  env vars, wired into railway.json's start command, so an admin
  account can be provisioned without needing Railway's console shell
- Brand the admin-interface theme (title, logo) and add a custom
  admin/index.html dashboard: live stat cards (matches, live now,
  channels, news) and a live-match management table over real data
- Add .gitignore and stop tracking committed __pycache__ files
